@paymentId = your-payment-id-here
@bookingId = your-booking-id-here

### Create Payment (Stripe)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookingId": "{{bookingId}}",
  "currency": "USD",
  "paymentMethod": "credit_card",
  "paymentProvider": "stripe",
  "metadata": {
    "customerNote": "Payment for vacation booking"
  }
}

###

### Create Payment with Custom Amount
POST http://localhost:3000/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookingId": "{{bookingId}}",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "paymentMethod": "credit_card",
  "paymentProvider": "stripe",
  "metadata": {
    "paymentType": "deposit"
  }
}

###

### Create Manual Payment (for admin/cash payments)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookingId": "{{bookingId}}",
  "amount": 1000.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "paymentMethod": "cash",
  "paymentProvider": "manual"
}

###

### Get Payment by ID
GET http://localhost:3000/api/payments/{{paymentId}}

###

### Update Payment Status (Admin only)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/payments/{{paymentId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "paymentStatus": "completed",
  "transactionId": "txn_1234567890",
  "metadata": {
    "note": "Payment verified and completed"
  }
}

###

### Process Full Refund (Admin only)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/refund
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Customer requested cancellation",
  "metadata": {
    "approvedBy": "manager@example.com"
  }
}

###

### Process Partial Refund (Admin only)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/payments/{{paymentId}}/refund
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 250.00,
  "reason": "Partial service issue - refunding 50% of payment",
  "metadata": {
    "issueType": "service_quality",
    "approvedBy": "manager@example.com"
  }
}

###
